H0.text: Which college was founded by Henry VI in 1440. King's College, Cambridge

H1.text: Which college was founded by Henry VI in 1440. Trinity College, Cambridge

H2.text: Which college was founded by Henry VI in 1440. Magdalen College, Oxford

H3.text: Which college was founded by Henry VI in 1440. Eton

A4.text: Eton College was founded by Henry VI as a charity school to provide free education to 70 poor boys who would then go on to King's College, Cambridge, founded by the same king in 1441.

A5.text: The name 'King's Scholars' refers to the foundation of the school by King Henry VI in 1440.
